.TH "__vmalloc_node" 9 "__vmalloc_node" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
__vmalloc_node \- allocate virtually contiguous memory
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void *" __vmalloc_node
.BI "(unsigned long size "  ","
.BI "unsigned long align "  ","
.BI "gfp_t gfp_mask "  ","
.BI "int node "  ","
.BI "const void *caller "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "size" 12
allocation size
.IP "align" 12
desired alignment
.IP "gfp_mask" 12
flags for the page level allocator
.IP "node" 12
node to use for allocation or NUMA_NO_NODE
.IP "caller" 12
caller's return address
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Allocate enough pages to cover \fIsize\fP from the page level allocator with
\fIgfp_mask\fP flags.  Map them into contiguous kernel virtual space.

Reclaim modifiers in \fIgfp_mask\fP - __GFP_NORETRY, __GFP_RETRY_MAYFAIL
and __GFP_NOFAIL are not supported

Any use of gfp flags outside of GFP_KERNEL should be consulted
with mm people.
.SH "RETURN"
pointer to the allocated memory or NULL on error
